{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|日|甲|ls=ic|t1=sun|t2=first}} – when the sun first rises.

In some late bronze inscriptions, it was also written as a {{Han compound|日|棗|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=sun|nocap=1}}, with {{zh-l|*棗}} sometimes simplified as {{zh-l|*朿}}. In ancient texts, {{och-l|蚤}} was often used instead.

{{zh-hanzi}}

# [[early]]; [[in advance]]; [[soon]]
#: {{zh-x|我 醒 得 很 早。|I woke up '''early'''.}}
#* {{zh-x|你 能 不 能 早 一點 來？|Can you be here a little '''earlier'''?}}
#* {{zh-x|請問，我 今天 早 走 一會兒{r} 行 嗎？|Please could I leave '''early''' today?}}
# [[long]] [[ago]]; for a long [[time]]
#: {{zh-x|他 早 走 了。|He left long ago.}}
#* {{zh-x|這 個 變壓器 已經 燒 毀 了，早 該 拆 換 一 個 新 的 了。|This transformer has burnt out. It should have been replaced a long time ago.}}
# (early) [[morning]]
#* {{zh-x|我 今 早 沒 有 見到 他。|I didn't see him this '''morning'''.}}
# [[good morning]]
#: {{zh-x|老師 早！|'''Good morning''', teacher!}}
# [[before]]; in the [[past]] time
#* {{zh-x|現在 這麼 匆忙，你 早 幹{gàn}嗎{má} 去 了。|So now you are in a hurry. What were you doing before?}}
